// Design Component Library File I/O
// Saves and loads COMPONENT subtrees to/from per-session component library files.
// Components are stored as .component.json files in {project}/.collab/sessions/{session}/components/.

FUNCTION getComponentsDir(project, session) -> string
  Returns the path to the components directory for a session.

---

FUNCTION sanitizeFilename(name) -> string
  Replace non-alphanumeric characters with underscores and lowercase the result,
  producing a safe filename from a component name.

---

FUNCTION saveComponentToLibrary(project, session, name, nodes) -> { success, path }  EXPORT
  Ensure the components directory exists.
  Write a .component.json file containing the name, current timestamp, and nodes array.
  Return the file path.

---

FUNCTION loadComponentFromLibrary(project, session, name) -> { name, nodes }     EXPORT
  Read the .component.json file for the given component name.
  IF file does not exist, throw a descriptive error suggesting list_library_components.
  IF file content is invalid JSON, throw a corrupted-data error.
  IF nodes array is missing or not an array, throw an invalid-format error.
  Return the component name and nodes array.

---

FUNCTION listLibraryComponents(project, session) -> Array<{ name, filename, savedAt }>  EXPORT
  Read the components directory. IF it doesn't exist, return empty array.
  For each .component.json file, parse and extract name, filename, and savedAt.
  Skip files with invalid content. Return the collected component metadata.
